isits to Google\n\nPlay. You can browse by date and by topic, and delete part or all of your\n\nactivity.\n\n\n\nGo to My Activity\n\n<https://myactivity.google.com/myactivity?utm_source=pp&hl=en>.\n\n\n\n*Google Dashboard*\n\n\n\nGoogle Dashboard allows you to manage information associated with specific\n\nproducts.\n\n\n\nGo to Dashboard <https://myaccount.google.com/dashboard?utm_source=pp&hl=en>\n\n.\n\n\n\n*Your Personal Information*\n\n\n\nManage your contact information, such as your name, email, and phone number.\n\n\n\nGo to Personal Info\n\n<https://myaccount.google.com/privacy?utm_source=pp&hl=en#personalinfo>.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use the Google Payments service provided by Google Payment Korea\n\nLLC, the Google Payments Privacy Notice below also provides details on how\n\nyour personal information is processed in that service.*\n\n\n\nGoogle Payments Privacy Notice:\n\nhttps://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice&ldl=ko\n\n\n\nYour purchases, credit history, and/or transaction information is available\n\nto you via a number of secure online tools we provide to all users to\n\naccess data. Sign in to your Google Account <https://myaccount.google.com/>\n\nto get an overview of the ways you use Google\'s services and access that\n\ndata.\n\n\n\nYou can also export your transaction history with Google Takeout:\n\n\n\n    1. Go to takeout.google.com.\n\n    2. Once the Google Takeout page opens, click *Deselect all*.\n\n    3. Select *Google Pay*.\n\n    4. At the bottom, click *Next step*.\n\n    5. In the 2nd section, select the file type, frequency, and destination.\n\n    6. Click *Create export*.\n\n\n\nFor more information, please visit the How to download your Google data\n\n<https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/3024190> Help Center article.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use Google Cloud service provided by Google, the Google Cloud\n\nPrivacy Notice below also provides details on how your personal information\n\nis processed in that service.*\n\n\n\nGoogle Cloud Privacy Notice:\n\nhttps://cloud.google.com/terms/cloud-privacy-notice\n\nмЭі мЭіл©ФмЭЉмЭА Google к≥Дм†Х л∞П мДЬлєДмК§мЭШ м§СмЪФнХЬ л≥Ак≤љмВђнХ≠мЭД мХМл†§лУЬл¶ђкЄ∞ мЬДнХі  \n\nл∞ЬмЖ°лРШмЧИмКµлЛИлЛ§.\n\n¬© 2023 Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA\n\n\n============================================================\n============================================================\nID: 1850b66346eccd76\nкµђлґД: мИШмЛ†\nм†Ьл™©: [кµђкЄА] к∞ЬмЭЄм†Хл≥і мЭімЪ©лВімЧ≠ нЖµмІА\n######################\nOutput:', 'role': 'user'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '("entity"<|>GOOGLE<|>ORGANIZATION<|>Google is a multinational technology company that specializes in Internet-related services and products, including search engines, online advertising technologies, cloud computing, software, and hardware.)\n##\n("entity"<|>GOOGLE PAYMENT KOREA LLC<|>ORGANIZATION<|>Google Payment Korea LLC is a subsidiary of Google that provides payment services in Korea.)\n##\n("entity"<|>KOREA<|>GEO<|>Korea is a country where Google provides its services and has specific privacy policies for its users.)\n##\n("entity"<|>MY ACTIVITY<|>EVENT<|>My Activity is a feature that allows users to review and control data created when using Google services.)\n##\n("entity"<|>GOOGLE DASHBOARD<|>EVENT<|>Google Dashboard is a tool that allows users to manage information associated with specific Google products.)\n##\n("entity"<|>PERSONAL INFO<|>EVENT<|>Personal Info is a feature that allows users to manage their contact information, such as name, email, and phone number.)\n##\n("relationship"<|>GOOGLE<|>GOOGLE PAYMENT KOREA LLC<|>Google Payment Korea LLC is a subsidiary of Google that provides payment services in Korea<|>7)\n##\n("relationship"<|>GOOGLE<|>KOREA<|>Google provides its services in Korea and has specific privacy policies for its users in the country<|>8)\n##\n("relati