КФ мВђлЮМ: csi10186@gmail.com\nлВ†мІЬ: Tue Mar 17 2026 18:46:06 GMT+0900 (нХЬкµ≠ нСЬм§АмЛЬ)\n\n[м≤®лґАнММмЭЉ]\n1. 5201a918-18d6-11f1-b005-9898fb898e98.csv | text/csv | 84 bytes\n\n[л≥ЄлђЄ]\nWe\'ll enable resource-based CUD sharing by default to maximize savings.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMY CONSOLE\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nл≤ИмЧ≠мЭі м†Ьк≥µлРШл©і л∞Фл°Ь к≥Дм†ХмЭШ кЄ∞л≥Є мЦЄмЦіл°Ь мЭі л©ФмЛЬмІАмЭШ мВђл≥ЄмЭД  \n\nл≥ілВілУЬл¶ђк≤†мКµлЛИлЛ§. мЭі к≥Љм†ХмЭА 1~2м£Љ м†ХлПД мЖМмЪФлР©лЛИлЛ§.\n\n\n\nHello Violin,\n\n\n\nStarting June 16, 2026, the default configuration for resource-based  \n\nCommitment Use Discount (CUD) sharing will change from disabled to enabled.  \n\nThis update is designed to maximize savings and reduce underused CUDs  \n\nacross your resources.\n\n\n\nWhat you need to know\n\n\n\nKey changes:\n\n\n\n\n\nNew billing accounts: All new billing accounts created on or after June 16,  \n\n2026 will have CUD sharing enabled by default.\n\nExisting billing accounts (no active resource-based CUDs): Accounts that do  \n\nnot have active resource-based CUDs as of June 16, 2026, will have their  \n\ndefault CUD sharing setting updated to enabled.\n\nExisting billing accounts (with active resource-based CUDs): If you have at  \n\nleast one active resource-based CUD on your billing account at the time of  \n\nthe change, your current settings will remain unchanged.\n\nFlexible management: You can enable or disable CUD sharing for your billing  \n\naccount at any time using the self-serve toggle in the Google Cloud Billing  \n\nconsole.\n\n\n\nPotential impact:\n\nThis change is designed to be value-additive. With sharing enabled, any  \n\nresource-based commitments you purchase can be applied to eligible  \n\nresources in any project linked to your billing account, rather than being  \n\nrestricted to a single project. This helps prevent "stranded" discounts and  \n\nmaximizes your total savings.\n\n\n\nWhat you need to do\n\n\n\nAction advised:\n\nNo immediate action is required to receive this benefit.\n\n\n\nHowever, if you prefer to keep your discounts isolated to a specific  \n\nproject, you may use the new self-serve toggle in the Google Cloud Billing  \n\nconsole to disable sharing at any time.\n\n\n\nTimelines:\n\nThe default update will take effect on June 16, 2026. You will have access  \n\nto the self-serve management tools in the Google Cloud Billing console  \n\nprior to this date to adjust your preferences.\n\n\n\nImpacted customers/accounts:\n\nThis change impacts new billing accounts and existing accounts without  \n\nactive resource-based CUDs.\n\nPlease refer to the attachment below (CSV file) for a list of the projects.\n\nWe\'re here to help\n\n\n\nFor more information on how resource-based CUD sharing works and how to  \n\nmanage it, please refer to our Share resource-based CUDs across projects  \n\ndocumentation.\n\n\n\nIf you have any questions or require assistance, please contact Google  \n\nCloud Support.\n\n\n\nThanks for choosing Google Cloud.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nвАУ The Google Cloud Team\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDOCUMENTATION\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSUPPORT\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n¬© 2026 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043\n\n\n\nYou\'ve received this mandatory service announcement to update you about  \n\nimportant changes to Google Cloud or your account.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nVisit GCP on GitHub Visit Google Cloud on LinkedIn Visit Google Cloud on  \n\nTwitter\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n============================================================\n============================================================\nID: 19cfaf776e9eeac6\nкµђлґД: мИШмЛ†\nм†Ьл™©: Re: [s0-yeon/GmailWeaver] #22 feat: м≤®лґАнММмЭЉ м≤Шл¶ђ к∞ЬмД† (мЫРл≥Є нММмЭЉмЭД мДЬл≤ДмЧР м†АмЮ•) (PR #28)\nл≥ілВЄ мВђлЮМ: uzichoi <notifications@github.com>\nл∞ЫлКФ мВђлЮМ: "s0-yeon/GmailWeaver" <GmailWeaver@noreply.github.com>\nлВ†мІЬ: Tue Mar 17 2026 17:44:07 GMT+0900 (нХЬкµ≠ нСЬм§АмЛЬ)\n\n[м≤®лґАнММмЭЉ]\nмЧЖмЭМ\n\n[л≥ЄлђЄ]\n@uzichoi requested your review on